-# Ghost Publisher
-
-Posts markdown articles to `intelligentrails.news` via Ghost Admin API.
-
-## One-time setup
-
-```bash
-pip install pyjwt requests markdown --break-system-packages
-```
-
-## Credentials
-
-Set these in your shell (or a `.env` loaded by your orchestrator):
-
-```
-GHOST_API_URL=https://intelligent-rails-1.ghost.io
-GHOST_ADMIN_API_KEY=<REDACTED>
-GHOST_CONTENT_API_KEY=<REDACTED> key>   # optional, not used for posting
-```
-
-Do **not** commit keys. Do **not** persist them to auto-memory.
-
-## Usage
-
-```bash
-python publish_to_ghost.py path/to/article.md \
-    --status draft \
-    --tags "Stablecoins,Banking"
-```
-
-- Default status is `draft` — safer. Switch to `--status published` when you want it live.
-- Title is pulled from the first `# H1`; override with `--title "..."`.
-- The first non-heading, non-HR line becomes the custom excerpt.
-- Markdown is rendered with `extra + smarty + sane_lists` then sent via `source=html`.
-
-### Feature image handling
-
-The script auto-scans the article's directory for a companion image matching `*teaser*`, `*hero*`, `*cover*`, or `*feature*` (`.png/.jpg/.jpeg/.webp`). Files whose name starts with the article basename win the tie-break. The first match is uploaded and set as `feature_image`. Alt text defaults to the article title.
-
-Override or disable:
-
-```bash
-python publish_to_ghost.py article.md --feature-image ./hero.png --feature-image-alt "Custom alt"
-python publish_to_ghost.py article.md --no-auto-image   # skip entirely
-```
-
-**Rule:** if an article directory contains a teaser/hero image, the script WILL attach it. Stop rediscovering this by hand.
-
-## Return value
-
-Prints the post id, status, live URL, and the direct edit link in the Ghost admin.
-
-## Known defaults / assumptions
-
-- `Accept-Version: v5.0` — Ghost v5 Admin API.
-- JWT expiry 5 minutes, `kid` = key id, HS256 over the hex-decoded secret.
-- `tags` arrive as name objects; Ghost will create missing tags on first use.
-- No feature image handling yet — add via `post_payload["feature_image"]` if needed.
-
